      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"mixed results\" is a bit vague lol. like, if you look at the actual data, isn't it pretty clear that these policies usually just cycle people through jail without actually fixing the root causes? it feels like the deterrence argument is kind of an outdated way to look at it compared to what sociologists are saying now.",
